Package slogo.compiler

Class SLogoTokenMaker

java.lang.Object
slogo.compiler.SLogoTokenMaker
public class SLogoTokenMaker
extends java.lang.Object
The SLogoTokenMaker class creates SLogoToken objects of the correct type given a user input. Calling make() will return an instance of the desired token, constructed with only a name as the "bare minimum". Tokens that require more parameters will later be filled in by the Compiler.

  • Method Details

    • make

      public SLogoToken make​(java.lang.String tokenType, java.lang.String inputString) throws SLogoException
      Creates a SLogoToken object from a String describing the type of token, and the user input string. In the case of SLogoUserDefinedCommand or SLogoVariable, the method will first search the Workspace for the a matching WorkspaceEntry. If none are found, the method creates a new entry of the correct subclass, adds it to the workspace, and returns it.
      Parameters:
      tokenType - String description of the token type, obtained from a .properties file.
      inputString - the user input String that is used to name the token.
      Returns:
      a SLogoToken object, or null if no object can be created from the given strings.
      Throws:
      SLogoException
